<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-05T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="958" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d958">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">561.35E1A/113: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-05T19:00:00-05:00">October 5, 1937—7
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>412. Your 631, October 5, 6 p.m. For your information and possible use, the
                        Department is to discuss this matter with Mr. Davis but can not do so before
                        the end of the week.</p>
                    <p>Report amply Council discussions on this point. What have Dominican and
                        Peruvian delegates had to say on this matter and as to their expectations or
                        plans for production for this quota year?</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>